{
  "texts": [
    "Empirical assessment is the only way to ensure their validity.",
    "Most models considered in applied machine learning are both too complicated and too closely tailored to their specific application to be generically justified.",
    "Applied machine learning researchers typically think about methodological rigour as demanding they implement \"cross validation\" procedures which estimate operationalized generalization concepts.",
    "The most critical such procedure is to split data into a portion used for training, i.e.",
    "model fitting, and a different portion used for testing [41]."
  ]
}